00:21:23,990 --> 00:21:28,160
will upset her more if she finds out later.

285
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:32,410
I first met her two years ago.

286
00:21:32,410 --> 00:21:35,040
From then until now,

287
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:38,850
she's been very worried about me and my brother.

288
00:21:38,850 --> 00:21:40,780
That is why.

289
00:21:46,890 --> 00:21:50,960
When I was eight years old,

290
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:53,060
my birth mother died.

291
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:56,920
I see.

292
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:00,770
I'm very sorry.

293
00:22:02,590 --> 00:22:06,530
I think she's always with me.

294
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:09,570
She told me that

295
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:13,870
she'll always be with me.

296
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:20,290
Please don't tell my stepmom what happened.

297
00:22:20,290 --> 00:22:22,660
Everything tonight was my fault.

298
00:22:22,660 --> 00:22:26,550
If you need to scold someone, please scold me.

299
00:22:26,550 --> 00:22:29,520
Nakwon didn't do anything wrong.

300
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:37,230
You said...

301
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:39,460
your name is Namu?

302
00:22:40,980 --> 00:22:43,570
It's a very lovely name.

303
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,740
Come over often, Namu.

304
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:51,950
And be good friends with Nakwon.

305
00:22:51,950 --> 00:22:55,360
She's strong-willed and does things without thinking.

306
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:57,630
She's a bit dangerous.

307
00:22:57,630 --> 00:23:00,250
Like a ticking bomb.

308
00:23:00,250 --> 00:23:04,100
I'd like you to look after her for me.

309
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:07,360
Could you do that?

310
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,530
Yes.

311
00:23:17,710 --> 00:23:21,110
Geez, it's freezing cold.

312
00:23:22,040 --> 00:23:24,510
Mom, I really want some hot chocolate, too.

313
00:23:32,260 --> 00:23:34,150
You're making him uncomfortable.

314
00:23:34,150 --> 00:23:36,400
Why don't you give him some space?

315
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,260
Nope. We're best friends, now.

316
00:23:39,260 --> 00:23:42,570
I announced that I'll continue to like him.

317
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:44,240
Didn't I?

318
00:23:45,330 --> 00:23:47,940
My daughter is so straightforward.

319
00:23:47,940 --> 00:23:49,480
You never play games...

320
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:52,110
nor play hard-to-get, right?

321
00:23:52,110 --> 00:23:54,640
What's that? Are you eating?

322
00:24:05,890 --> 00:24:09,820
I guess you could think so.

323
00:24:09,820 --> 00:24:11,620
My face...

324
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:14,870
could be intimidating for some.

325
00:24:17,140 --> 00:24:20,010
Mom, I want hot chocolate too. No, I'll make my own.

326
00:24:20,010 --> 00:24:21,830
I have my arms and legs.

327
00:24:32,340 --> 00:24:33,510
Where's my piggy?

328
00:24:33,510 --> 00:24:36,850
That troublemaker got into more...

329
00:24:36,890 --> 00:24:39,190
How can you call your

330
00:24:39,190 --> 00:24:41,420
teenange daughter, "piggy"?

331
00:24:43,290 --> 00:24:44,760
Hello, sir.

332
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:46,600
Oh, hello.

333
00:24:54,740 --> 00:24:56,700
Have a good night.

334
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,310
Thank you

335
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:00,810
for these.

336
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:02,140
Sure.

337
00:25:02,140 --> 00:25:05,290
I'll make you more when you finish.

338
00:25:05,290 --> 00:25:08,510
Bring your sister next time.

339
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:16,420
Namu, it's cold. Wear this.

340
00:25:18,730 --> 00:25:22,060
You could catch a cold.

341
00:25:24,060 --> 00:25:26,040
There you go.

342
00:25:29,940 --> 00:25:32,040
All right, get home safe.

343
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:35,210
And be good friends with... no.

344
00:25:35,220 --> 00:25:38,150
Keep a good distance but still be good friends.

345
00:25:38,150 --> 00:25:41,510
You know it's wrong to bully others, right?

346
00:25:41,510 --> 00:25:45,030
Even though our Nakwon's slightly odd,

347
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:48,930
try to understand, like Jesus or Buddha.

348
00:25:48,930 --> 00:25:50,790
Stop it, really!

349
00:25:50,790 --> 00:25:53,690
Are you really my dad?

350
00:25:53,690 --> 00:25:56,560
Bye, Namu. See you tomorrow.

351
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:55,800
Those are my clothes.

352
00:26:57,820 --> 00:27:00,530
Were you at my house?

353
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:02,790
Hello.

354
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:04,860
I suppose...

355
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:07,310
Nakwon was with you.

356
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,810
My apologies.

357
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,380
She's my one and only sister.

358
00:27:14,250 --> 00:27:16,920
I don't care if you spend time with her.

359
00:27:17,580 --> 00:27:20,050
But don't make me worry like today,

360
00:27:20,050 --> 00:27:22,290
ever again.

361
00:27:22,310 --> 00:27:24,520
I'm asking you a favor, and

362
00:27:25,620 --> 00:27:27,390
also giving a warning.

363
00:27:49,510 --> 00:27:53,690
Hello? Sohjin is here.

364
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,890
Your brotherâ€”

365
00:27:57,490 --> 00:27:59,530
Hyeonmu brought her here.

366
00:27:59,530 --> 00:28:01,360
Okay.

367
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:06,560
Geez, what's going on?

368
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:11,410
Hey, Hyeonmu.

369
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,930
What is that?

370
00:28:13,940 --> 00:28:16,510
Are those blood stains?

371
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:18,070
Did you fight again?

372
00:28:18,070 --> 00:28:21,270
- Did you get hurt?
- Of course, not.

373
00:28:21,270 --> 00:28:22,980
No one can beat me.

374
00:28:22,980 --> 00:28:25,110
Then, this is someone else's blood?

375
00:28:25,110 --> 00:28:28,220
My god, what's wrong with you?

376
00:28:28,220 --> 00:28:30,260
How will you make up for what you've done?

377
00:28:30,260 --> 00:28:32,130
It's not your concern.

378
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:35,520
You don't care much about me anyhow.

379
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:37,120
What did you say?

380
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:40,760
Namu kisses up to you and calls you mother.

381
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:43,410
You only care about him.

382
00:28:43,410 --> 00:28:47,060
He's smart and he listens to you.

383
00:28:47,060 --> 00:28:48,770
As for me?

384
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:53,380
Nobody cares about me.

385
00:28:53,380 --> 00:28:55,570
It's all right.

386
00:28:55,570 --> 00:28:58,320
You're not the first.

387
00:28:58,320 --> 00:28:59,890
The other women were also like that.

388
00:28:59,890 --> 00:29:02,190
How can you say such a thing?

389
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:06,050
Even if I couldn't treat you like my own son for the past two years,

390
00:29:06,050 --> 00:29:07,850
I still cooked and washed your clothes.

391
00:29:07,850 --> 00:29:09,660
I even gave you an allowance.

392
00:29:09,660 --> 00:29:11,400
How can you speak to me that way?

393
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:13,960
Let's get going, now.

394
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:16,040
My clothes will smell.

395
00:29:24,100 --> 00:29:27,480
Why didn't you tell Dad before leaving?

396
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:29,220
You said that he was home at the time.

397
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:30,920
Why did you leave without saying anything?

398
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:33,710
It's because...

399
00:29:33,710 --> 00:29:37,630
Why? Did he scold you?

400
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:40,580
Mommy.

401
00:29:40,580 --> 00:29:44,200
To be honest...

402
00:29:56,980 --> 00:29:58,970
What did you say?

403
00:30:10,990 --> 00:30:14,660
Did you walk your cute friend home?

404
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:18,730
Yes.

405
00:30:36,270 --> 00:30:37,980
Namu,

406
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:42,780
do you remember what I told you on the hill?

407
00:30:44,580 --> 00:30:47,600
Of course, you do. You're smart.

408
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:51,020
You usually don't forget what you see and hear.

409
00:30:51,060 --> 00:30:54,260
- Yes.
- What did I tell you?

410
00:30:54,290 --> 00:30:55,890
Tell me my exact words.

411
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:57,610
People like us...

412
00:30:57,610 --> 00:31:01,830
and the dog I saved earlier.

413
00:31:01,830 --> 00:31:04,170
What's the difference?

414
00:31:06,210 --> 00:31:07,920
Nothing.

415
00:31:09,420 --> 00:31:11,620
We're the same.

416
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:13,610
We're both animals.

417
00:31:14,610 --> 00:31:17,530
Yeah, that's right.

418
00:31:17,530 --> 00:31:19,280
Humans are animals...

419
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:22,150
who prey on each other.

420
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:28,530
This world's a huge cage where the humans are locked up in.

421
00:31:28,530 --> 00:31:29,790
The weak won't last.

422
00:31:29,790 --> 00:31:33,000
Only the strong survive.

423
00:31:33,030 --> 00:31:35,670
In this cage-like world,

424
00:31:35,670 --> 00:31:38,550
that's the only way to survive.

425
00:31:58,170 --> 00:32:00,000
Did you see that?

426
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:02,740
Only merciless strength is what makes you strong.

427
00:32:02,740 --> 00:32:04,170
Sympathy or affection...

428
00:32:04,170 --> 00:32:08,270
only makes humans weak and pathetic.

429
00:32:08,270 --> 00:32:12,280
Those have no value in our lives.

430
00:32:12,300 --> 00:32:14,480
You must become strong like me.

431
00:32:14,510 --> 00:32:16,070
You know what?

432
00:32:17,150 --> 00:32:20,860
I only trust my children.

433
00:32:24,050 --> 00:32:26,190
It's only my children...

434
00:32:26,190 --> 00:32:28,730
who will not stab me in the back.

435
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:32,100
That's right.

436
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:34,400
That's my boy.

437
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:42,540
That's my blood, indeed.

438
00:32:47,070 --> 00:32:49,570
From now on,

439
00:32:49,570 --> 00:32:51,910
don't do anything dangerous like that.

440
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:55,410
Don't go into my basement workshop without my permission.

441
00:32:55,410 --> 00:32:59,490
Don't ever disobey me again.

442
00:33:00,430 --> 00:33:02,920
Or I'll get furious.

443
00:33:03,820 --> 00:33:05,600
Do you understand?

444
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:09,490
Yes.

445
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:12,010
Okay.

446
00:33:12,030 --> 00:33:15,100
You should get some sleep for school, tomorrow.

447
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:18,970
You excel at everything.

448
00:33:18,970 --> 00:33:21,910
You are the only son that I'm proud of.

449
00:33:22,610 --> 00:33:25,720
You're different from Hyeonmu.

450
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:30,760
You've never disappointed me, not once.

451
00:33:30,780 --> 00:33:33,130
Good night, my son.

452
00:33:33,130 --> 00:33:36,460
You're my precious.

453
00:33:36,460 --> 00:33:39,170
You're my treasure.

454
00:33:52,570 --> 00:33:54,920
If you can't get rid of it,

455
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:56,970
I'll do it for you.

456
00:33:56,990 --> 00:33:59,290
Every useless thing...

457
00:33:59,310 --> 00:34:01,990
that puts you in any danger.

458
00:34:02,010 --> 00:34:03,860
Nothing can exist...

459
00:34:03,860 --> 00:34:06,580
for humans to become strong.

460
00:34:06,580 --> 00:34:08,960
So get rid of it.

461
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:11,320
Get rid of all the obstacles.

462
00:34:22,330 --> 00:34:23,870
No.

463
00:34:23,870 --> 00:34:26,210
I won't forget you.

464
00:34:26,210 --> 00:34:29,620
Because I like you.

465
00:34:30,450 --> 00:34:32,210
Namu, wear this.

466
00:34:32,210 --> 00:34:35,060
You could catch a cold.

467
00:34:35,060 --> 00:34:38,690
You're like a genuine tree, just like your name.

468
00:34:38,690 --> 00:34:40,250
That's why I like you.

469
00:34:40,260 --> 00:34:43,960
You're just like a real tree.

470
00:34:54,540 --> 00:34:59,070
I'll protect you from everything that makes you...

471
00:34:59,100 --> 00:35:01,780
weak and pathetic.
